⚙️ Technical Architecture

This project separates data generation from the frontend UI.

The entire system is static and hosted on GitHub Pages.


---

📦 Data Sources

1️⃣ Relic Data

Source: WFCD (warframe-relic-data)
Generated file: data/Relics.min.json

Contains:

All relic names

Drop tables

Drop chances



---

2️⃣ Platinum Price Data

Source: Warframe.market API
Generated file: data/prices.json

Uses:

90-day median sell price

Exact item name matching


The frontend never calls the API directly.
All pricing data is pre-generated by workflows.


---

3️⃣ Vault Status

Source: Official Warframe Wiki – Void Relic page

Specifically the table:

> “Unvaulted / Available Relics”



Relics listed in that table are marked as:

true  = Available (Green)
false = Vaulted (Red)

Generated file:

data/vaultStatus.json

Script:

scripts/update_vault_status.py


---

🔄 GitHub Actions Workflows

The automation system is designed as a sequential pipeline.


---

🔁 Full Workflow Chain

Update Vault Status (Wiki)
↓
Update Relics + Prices
↓
Deploy UI


---

1️⃣ Update Vault Status (Weekly)

Scrapes Warframe Wiki

Generates vaultStatus.json

Commits only if changes exist

Runs weekly via scheduled cron (Friday 21:00 UTC)

Can also be run manually



---

2️⃣ Update Relics + Prices

Triggered when:

Vault workflow completes successfully

OR manually dispatched


Generates:

Relics.min.json

prices.json


Additionally:

Re-runs vault status generation to ensure newly added relics are classified immediately


This prevents new relics from appearing without color (grey).

Commits only if data changed.


---

3️⃣ Deploy UI

Triggered when:

Heavy workflow completes

OR manually dispatched

Deploys static site to GitHub Pages

Publishes latest data + UI


No backend server required.


